title: Whereas the late Parliament dissolving themselves and resigning their powers and authorities, the government of the Common-wealth of England, Scotland, and Ireland, by a Lord Protector, and successive triennial parliaments, is now established ...
author: England and Wales. Privy Council.
notes: At head of title: By the council.
"Given at White-Hall, this sixteenth day of December, 1653."
Reproduction of original in the Union Theological Seminary Library, New York.
